        <p><strong>FileMaker Pro</strong> is a cross-platform relational database application from <strong>FileMaker Inc</strong>, formerly <strong>Claris</strong>, a subsidiary of <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Apple Inc', 'C'); ?>.</p>
        <p>It integrates a database engine with a <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('GUI', 'IT'); ?> based interface, allowing users to modify the database by dragging new elements into layouts, screens, or forms.</p>
        <p>FileMaker evolved from a <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('DOS', 'OS'); ?> application, but was then developed primarily for the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Apple Macintosh', 'ITH'); ?>.</p>
        <p>Since 1992 it has been available for <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Microsoft Windows', 'OS'); ?> and <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Mac OS', 'OS'); ?>, and can be used in a cross-platform environment.</p>
        <p>FileMaker server briefly ran on <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Linux', 'OS'); ?>, but Linux support was abandoned with FileMaker 7, and the server currently runs only on <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Windows Server', 'OS'); ?> or <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('OS X Server', 'OS'); ?>.</p>
        <p>It is available in desktop, server, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('iOS', 'OS'); ?> and web-delivery configurations.</p>
